## Helpers

Helpers contain view-specific logic and formatting.

### Helper Structure

```ruby
# app/helpers/articles_helper.rb

module ArticlesHelper
  def article_status_badge(article)
    color = case article.status
            when 'published' then 'bg-green-100 text-green-800'
            when 'draft' then 'bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800'
            when 'archived' then 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-800'
            else 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-800'
            end
    
    content_tag :span, article.status.titleize,
                class: "px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold #{color}"
  end
  
  def format_reading_time(article)
    minutes = article.reading_time
    pluralize(minutes, "minute") + " read"
  end
  
  def article_published_date(article)
    return "Not published" unless article.published_at
    
    if article.published_at > 1.year.ago
      article.published_at.strftime("%B %d, %Y")
    else
      article.published_at.strftime("%Y")
    end
  end
  
  def render_article_metadata(article)
    content_tag :div, class: "text-sm text-gray-600" do
      safe_join([
        content_tag(:span, "By #{article.user.name}"),
        " • ",
        content_tag(:time, article_published_date(article), datetime: article.published_at&.iso8601),
        " • ",
        content_tag(:span, format_reading_time(article))
      ])
    end
  end
end
```

### Helper Rules

**Use Helpers for View Logic:**
```ruby
# Good: Helper method
def format_price(amount)
  number_to_currency(amount, unit: "$", precision: 2)
end

# Good: Helper returns HTML
def status_badge(status)
  color = status == 'active' ? 'green' : 'gray'
  content_tag :span, status.titleize, class: "badge badge-#{color}"
end

# Bad: Business logic in helper
def calculate_discount(user, product)
  # This belongs in a model or service object
  if user.premium?
    product.price * 0.8
  else
    product.price
  end
end
```
